  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NGO Support / Improvement of Primary-level Maternal Health Services in Ibadan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to improve the quality of antenatal_ delivery and post-natal care in 19 primary health centres in Ibadan_ by introducing the use of simple guidelines_ flow-charts and other job-aids in clinical work. The tools will be developed by local experts adhering to national recommendations. Supervision and on-th-job training are provided to the health workers by 3 midwives who rotate weekly in the health centres. It is expected that improved quality of care will encourage service utilization. Local communities are sensitized. Data is collected to demonstrate the current situation of primary health care to the local policy makers.</narrative>
  </description>
